00:38:38.190 --> 00:38:40.700
AUDIENCE: How do
you tackle fatigue?

00:38:40.700 --> 00:38:45.792
So people, like these brands, if
everyone followed your advice,

00:38:45.792 --> 00:38:47.250
then everyone is
going to find ways

00:38:47.250 --> 00:38:49.370
to be more relevant
and more relevant,

00:38:49.370 --> 00:38:52.750
and humans only have so much
attention that they can focus.

00:38:52.750 --> 00:38:55.370
So is there a way
to handle customers

00:38:55.370 --> 00:38:57.570
just getting fatigued of
being bombarded constantly

00:38:57.570 --> 00:38:59.121
by these personalized messages?

00:38:59.121 --> 00:39:00.120
ANDREA COVILLE: I agree.

00:39:00.120 --> 00:39:01.578
And that's why I
started it the way

00:39:01.578 --> 00:39:05.400
I did, because I think people
start self-selecting just

00:39:05.400 --> 00:39:08.140
when they begin their day
about what they want to do.

00:39:08.140 --> 00:39:12.670
So in this day and age, to
be able to connect with you--

00:39:12.670 --> 00:39:15.630
which, from the starting
point, you have to be relevant.

00:39:15.630 --> 00:39:16.410
That's the point.

00:39:16.410 --> 00:39:19.240
First of all, you have
to know enough about you

00:39:19.240 --> 00:39:20.780
or a brand that
would appeal to you

00:39:20.780 --> 00:39:23.450
to get that to break through.

00:39:23.450 --> 00:39:26.454
And it's going to get more
intense, not less intense.

00:39:26.454 --> 00:39:28.120
And I think that's
the thing that brands

00:39:28.120 --> 00:39:31.900
need to understand-- the
power of just creating

00:39:31.900 --> 00:39:34.320
more and more information
for us at every-- I mean,

00:39:34.320 --> 00:39:37.280
pretty soon I'm sure it will
be in every device we use,

00:39:37.280 --> 00:39:40.950
there'll be some ability
to interact with content.

00:39:40.950 --> 00:39:42.960
That content has to be relevant.

00:39:42.960 --> 00:39:46.710
And the other point is, you
can't assume you are relevant.

00:39:46.710 --> 00:39:48.310
I think the biggest
mistake companies

00:39:48.310 --> 00:39:51.179
make are they assume they
have a great conversation

00:39:51.179 --> 00:39:51.970
with their clients.

00:39:51.970 --> 00:39:53.690
They assume they,
or their customers,

00:39:53.690 --> 00:39:54.970
they know what they want.

00:39:54.970 --> 00:39:55.610
And they don't.

00:39:55.610 --> 00:39:59.770
And it's really hard to regain
relevance once you've lost it.

00:39:59.770 --> 00:40:02.450
If you're making an
assumption that apps aren't

00:40:02.450 --> 00:40:04.562
important in the
business environment

00:40:04.562 --> 00:40:09.130
